external_knowledge:
- 'frequently checked' refers to checking more than 10 times;
- 'companies trading above their usual price levels' refers to those whose adjusted closing prices are above the average for the stock for the year 2022;
- 'finance analysts' refers to users with the role 'analyst' and belong to the 'finance' department.

- 'Bustling activity' implies high trading volumes; 
- 'Peak trading days' refers to the days with the highest total stock volumes traded;
- 'Respective ranks' indicate the ranking of these days based on total volume, with the highest volume getting the top rank.

- "stars of the financial sky" metaphorically refers to the stocks;
- "shine brightly on the NASDAQ stage" refers to the stocks being traded on the NASDAQ exchange;
- "spotted through the telescope of our access logs" metaphorically refers to the count of times these stocks have been recorded in the access logs.

sql:
SELECT source_id, AVG(num_records) as average_records_per_import
FROM data_imports
GROUP BY source_id;

SELECT s.stock_symbol, dp.date, dp.volume
FROM stocks s
JOIN daily_prices dp ON s.stock_id = dp.stock_id;

SELECT AVG(num_records) AS avg_records
FROM data_imports
WHERE source_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id)
FROM access_logs
WHERE stock_id = (SELECT stock_id FROM stocks WHERE stock_symbol = 'AAPL');
